meta {
  name: Steam Signup Prefill
  type: http
  seq: 18
}

get {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/steam/signup-prefill?token={{steamSignupToken}}
  body: none
  auth: none
}

params:query {
  token: {{steamSignupToken}}
}

docs {
  # Steam Signup Prefill

  Returns the Steam identity (steam id, persona name, avatar URL, profile URL)
  carried by a verified Steam signup token. Used by the `/register` page to
  prefill the form when the user is redirected from the Steam OpenID callback.

  Idempotent and read-only — the token is consumed only when the signup is
  actually submitted via `POST /api/auth/register/steam`.

  ## Query Parameters

  - **token** (required): the JWT received as `?steam_token=` after the Steam
    OpenID callback. Short-lived (~10 min).

  ## Responses

  - **200 OK**: `{ steamId, steamDisplayName, steamAvatarUrl, steamProfileUrl }`.
    Display name / avatar / profile URL may be `null` when the Steam Web API
    was unreachable at token-issuance time.
  - **400 Bad Request**: invalid, tampered, or expired token.

  ## Variables

  Set `steamSignupToken` in your environment, or paste the JWT in-line.
}
